reviews.text: Great bar staff and fun, Frenchy vibe.. can get a bit packed and you can struggle to find a perch for your beverage.. but they make generous gin and tonics!

Amazing place for homesick Frenchies. We had a lot of fun and were even able to select some French songs we wanted to listen at.
Gian and also the other waiters were very nice.
A great little hideaway spot for good food and a  spot of wine...or three. The staff was attentive and friendly. I enjoyed sitting in the doorway and watching Hong Kong live through its day.

Nice location. quick dinner before an evening event we had to attend in the area. We had a couple glasses of wine, the cold meat platter and also the chicken to share. All very good and everyone was happy. Fast friendly service, and a nice atmosphere.
Great food and wine for France lovers.

result.name: Pastis

reviews.text:
Lieu atypique, personnel très, très sympathique ! 
À conseiller notamment à partir de mardi/mercredi (un peu plus fréquenté).
Vous aurez la possibilité d'y manger «sur le pouce» des assiettes de charcuterie bien fournies, pour poursuivre votre soirée dans une excellente ambiance bon enfant. 
N'oubliez pas de goûter au cocktail maison (get27 +...pastis, évidemment), bien glacé il est très agréable !
Great bar staff and fun, Frenchy vibe.. can get a bit packed and you can struggle to find a perch for your beverage.. but they make generous gin and tonics!

Amazing place for homesick Frenchies. We had a lot of fun and were even able to select some French songs we wanted to listen at.
Gian and also the other waiters were very nice.
法國色的酒吧餐廰，食物質素很高，員工服務态度很好，友善，值得一試！
A great little hideaway spot for good food and a  spot of wine...or three. The staff was attentive and friendly. I enjoyed sitting in the doorway and watching Hong Kong live through its day.

result.adr_address: 49 Elgin St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Bouchon Bistro Francais

reviews.text: Family of 2 Adults and young teens. Loved the cosy atmosphere. Staff were extremely professional and attentive (but not too attentive). All our meals terrific and meat was soft and not chewy at all. Could not recommend highly enough. Air con was absolutely fine at 7pm, but during the middle of the day it may be warm as others commented.
One of my favorite French restaurants in town. Cozy and unpretentious, the focus here is on the classics - think beef bourguignon, duck confit, bouillabaisse...- which are all very well prepared.
Nice lunch at reasonable price. Online reservation is available. They have both indoor and outdoor seats.
Pleasant french bistro, good kitchen and nice selection of wines. The lunch menu is always delightful.

What a lovely gem right in the heart of Soho. The Bouchon restaurant has an outstanding lunch sets that are absolutely worth the detour. The food is delicious, the place is cozy and the service is outstanding. Highly recommend the frits steak!
